pullRequest.body:
Added a class `HasRankNullity` consisting of the rings that satisfy the rank-nullity theorem.
Generalized the corollaries of the rank-nullity theorem from division rings to rings satisfying the class,
and moved them into a new file `LinearAlgebra.Dimension.RankNullity`.

Are we sure it holds?

I'm fairly certain that it holds. A domain that is not Ore is of infinite rank (see Cohn's *Skew Field* Proposition 1.3.6) and thus does not satisfy strong rank condition. Hence domains with strong rank condition are Ore and we can mimic the proof here.
Nice! Since this is probably not very well known, do you mind add the reference?

It's OK if you do it in later PR; I only need to use the ring version.
